1
00:00:19,667 --> 00:00:20,767
You wanted to talk to me?

2
00:00:20,833 --> 00:00:22,000
Are you mad at me?

3
00:00:22,067 --> 00:00:24,667
So, it's my fault that my
standards are high

4
00:00:24,733 --> 00:00:27,400
and you can't live up
to those standards?

5
00:00:27,467 --> 00:00:30,333
Now I know why you and Mikoy
didn't last long.

6
00:00:30,400 --> 00:00:33,300
What you call standards
is merely to hide

7
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:36,500
that you are a sad, little girl.

8
00:00:36,567 --> 00:00:37,533
Is the presentation finished?

9
00:00:37,600 --> 00:00:39,733
- Hey, Mikoy.
- I'll just fetch Hazel.

10
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:40,900
What happened?

11
00:00:40,967 --> 00:00:42,600
Celeste, even if you don't
tell me,

12
00:00:42,667 --> 00:00:44,433
I can see right through you.

13
00:00:44,500 --> 00:00:47,067
You hide behind this façade
of success.

14
00:00:47,133 --> 00:00:50,000
Successful fashion designer
engaged to be married

15
00:00:50,067 --> 00:00:51,500
to a business tycoon.

16
00:00:51,567 --> 00:00:53,567
You project this aura
that you're happy

17
00:00:53,633 --> 00:00:56,767
because you're on top
of the world, but you are sad.

18
00:00:56,833 --> 00:00:58,067
Where are you going?

19
00:00:58,133 --> 00:01:00,233
Does it hurt to hear the truth?

20
00:01:00,300 --> 00:01:03,067
I hate to tell you this
but it's time for you to go.

21
00:01:03,133 --> 00:01:05,933
Stop using this community
service as an excuse

22
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:09,567
for Mikoy to love you again
and your whole family.

23
00:01:09,667 --> 00:01:11,167
They were happy even
if you're not here.

24
00:01:11,233 --> 00:01:13,800
And they will continue to be
happy even if you leave.

25
00:01:13,867 --> 00:01:15,500
Get off me!

26
00:01:16,267 --> 00:01:20,500
Grandma, how did you convince
them to join my project?

27
00:01:20,567 --> 00:01:23,500
I told them how kind you are,

28
00:01:23,567 --> 00:01:27,600
and you have a good heart
for poor people like us.

29
00:01:27,667 --> 00:01:29,733
More people are coming.

30
00:01:29,800 --> 00:01:32,000
- Really?
- Yes.

31
00:01:32,067 --> 00:01:33,600
Thank you.

32
00:01:33,667 --> 00:01:35,500
Did you see what she did to me?

33
00:01:35,567 --> 00:01:37,500
- That's enough.
- I'm just trying to help here

34
00:01:37,567 --> 00:01:40,167
but if Celeste's attitude
is like that,

35
00:01:40,233 --> 00:01:42,333
I don't know what to do.

36
00:01:42,433 --> 00:01:43,467
I said enough.

37
00:01:43,533 --> 00:01:44,633
That's enough.

38
00:01:44,700 --> 00:01:46,233
Are you siding with her?

39
00:01:46,300 --> 00:01:47,767
Unbelievable!

40
00:01:47,833 --> 00:01:49,233
I prepared it myself.

41
00:01:49,300 --> 00:01:51,533
You've really perfected this.

42
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:54,067
And that's one thing that
really impresses me.

43
00:01:54,133 --> 00:01:57,167
If there's one thing that
you want to learn,

44
00:01:57,233 --> 00:01:59,167
you become really,
really good at it.

45
00:01:59,233 --> 00:02:00,900
You really are a good guy.

46
00:02:00,967 --> 00:02:03,633
You never made me feel bad
or inadequate.

47
00:02:03,700 --> 00:02:05,267
And for that I'm thankful.

48
00:02:05,333 --> 00:02:07,533
The truth is, I know
it's not your fault.

49
00:02:07,600 --> 00:02:08,533
I was there.

50
00:02:08,600 --> 00:02:10,100
I saw everything.

51
00:02:10,167 --> 00:02:12,033
Don't side with me.

52
00:02:12,100 --> 00:02:13,700
You should side with Hazel.

53
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:19,167
In fact, to be honest,
I was just being unfair.

54
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:24,233
I was unfair to her
because of you.

55
00:02:24,300 --> 00:02:25,267
Huh?

56
00:02:25,333 --> 00:02:26,767
Wait.

57
00:02:28,667 --> 00:02:30,100
Why?

58
00:02:30,167 --> 00:02:32,067
What's my fault?

59
00:02:35,233 --> 00:02:36,500
Seriously?

60
00:02:37,633 --> 00:02:41,133
You don't know
what you did to me?

61
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:45,433
So, what is this I feel?
Imagination?

62
00:02:46,467 --> 00:02:49,333
Tell me. What's my fault?

63
00:02:49,433 --> 00:02:54,833
You have the nerve to say
that it's me who gave up on us.

64
00:03:02,633 --> 00:03:05,200
I will not come with you!

65
00:03:05,267 --> 00:03:07,800
Whether you like it or not,
we will go back to Sorsogon.

66
00:03:07,867 --> 00:03:09,700
What is your problem?

67
00:03:09,767 --> 00:03:12,233
Your ambition blinded you.

68
00:03:12,300 --> 00:03:14,567
My ambition?
Isn't this our dream?

69
00:03:14,633 --> 00:03:16,200
This is not just my dream.

70
00:03:16,267 --> 00:03:18,167
This is not the life
I dreamed of.

71
00:03:18,233 --> 00:03:19,633
What do you want?

72
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:21,633
A simple life.

73
00:03:21,733 --> 00:03:23,067
You know, that's the problem
with you.

74
00:03:23,133 --> 00:03:24,867
You get easily contented.

75
00:03:24,933 --> 00:03:27,400
The problem with you is you
don't get contented.

76
00:03:28,500 --> 00:03:30,333
That's why you don't achieve
anything in your life

77
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:31,567
because of your attitude.

78
00:03:31,633 --> 00:03:34,600
You know, I forced myself
here in Manila.

79
00:03:34,667 --> 00:03:36,667
But I'm tired.

80
00:03:36,733 --> 00:03:39,667
I'm tired of rejection.

81
00:03:39,733 --> 00:03:41,467
I'm tired of that.

82
00:03:43,133 --> 00:03:47,500
Let's go home while I still have
respect for myself.

83
00:03:47,567 --> 00:03:51,300
If you're already tired,
if you don't like it anymore,

84
00:03:51,367 --> 00:03:53,500
don't involve me.

85
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:56,667
It's not my fault if I'm more
successful than you.

86
00:03:56,733 --> 00:03:58,367
You are so selfish.
That's what you are.

87
00:03:58,433 --> 00:04:00,167
I'm selfish?

88
00:04:00,233 --> 00:04:01,433
Me?

89
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:03,200
Why?

90
00:04:03,267 --> 00:04:05,467
Is it bad to pursue in life?

91
00:04:05,533 --> 00:04:07,600
Is it bad to dream?

92
00:04:07,667 --> 00:04:11,167
You are very insensitive.

93
00:04:11,767 --> 00:04:15,267
You are insensitive
because of your dreams.

94
00:04:15,333 --> 00:04:21,467
Mikoy, I'm thankful for
everything that you did for me.

95
00:04:21,533 --> 00:04:27,233
But wherever I am now,
I worked hard for it.

96
00:04:29,867 --> 00:04:32,233
I worked hard for that.

97
00:04:32,300 --> 00:04:35,900
So don't ever tell me
that I'm selfish.

98
00:04:35,967 --> 00:04:38,833
Don't judge me because
I'm not like that.

99
00:04:38,900 --> 00:04:41,900
This conversation
is pointless.

100
00:04:41,967 --> 00:04:44,567
If you don't want to come
with me to Sorsogon,

101
00:04:44,633 --> 00:04:46,233
I will not force you.

102
00:04:47,767 --> 00:04:49,500
I'll be the one to leave.

103
00:05:35,333 --> 00:05:37,233
How can I not be pissed off?

104
00:05:39,233 --> 00:05:41,433
How can I not be angry?

105
00:05:44,667 --> 00:05:46,800
You left me.

106
00:05:48,367 --> 00:05:50,533
You turned your back on me.

107
00:05:53,067 --> 00:05:57,500
I just wanted you to wait
for me...

108
00:06:00,167 --> 00:06:02,300
to believe in me...

109
00:06:04,100 --> 00:06:10,900
that someday I can
fulfill my dreams.

110
00:06:16,500 --> 00:06:18,167
But I did.

111
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:27,667
I believed in you.

112
00:06:36,833 --> 00:06:39,100
I also made a gamble.

113
00:06:42,067 --> 00:06:44,000
I also sacrificed, right?

114
00:06:44,067 --> 00:06:45,767
Have you forgotten?

115
00:06:47,133 --> 00:06:48,633
You were there.

116
00:06:51,067 --> 00:06:52,933
Have you forgotten,
Celeste?

117
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:55,567
Have you forgotten everything
that I endured?

118
00:06:58,567 --> 00:07:03,467
Have you forgotten everything
I did

119
00:07:03,533 --> 00:07:06,667
just to fulfill your dream?

120
00:07:06,733 --> 00:07:11,567
I did everything just to
fulfill your dream.

121
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:21,633
I did everything for you.

122
00:07:21,700 --> 00:07:23,467
What I can't take is you

123
00:07:23,533 --> 00:07:26,433
neglecting yourself
for your dream.

124
00:07:31,633 --> 00:07:34,733
Celeste, you haven't touched
the food I prepared for you.

125
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:36,233
You should eat first.

126
00:07:37,667 --> 00:07:39,533
I'll finish this first.

127
00:07:41,133 --> 00:07:42,633
You should rest.

128
00:07:44,533 --> 00:07:46,933
That's too much hardship.

129
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:49,467
It's you who should rest.
That's enough.

130
00:07:57,033 --> 00:07:59,233
I can still do this.
I'll just finish this.

131
00:08:09,333 --> 00:08:10,900
Are you okay?

132
00:08:18,267 --> 00:08:19,400
Ah...

133
00:08:20,033 --> 00:08:21,167
Celeste?

134
00:08:22,467 --> 00:08:23,500
Celeste?

135
00:08:26,933 --> 00:08:28,167
Celeste?

136
00:08:34,367 --> 00:08:38,533
That's when I realized
that you'll do anything

137
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:40,900
for that stupid dream of yours.

138
00:08:42,800 --> 00:08:45,567
You were so focused on
what you wanted to happen.

139
00:08:45,633 --> 00:08:47,467
You forgot everything.

140
00:08:48,933 --> 00:08:50,933
And I can't watch that.

141
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:55,600
The more I can't watch you
selling yourself.

142
00:08:56,233 --> 00:08:58,033
That's why I asked you
to choose.

143
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:05,600
I asked you to choose,
me or your dreams...

144
00:09:08,300 --> 00:09:10,333
because I have to protect you.

145
00:09:11,533 --> 00:09:14,633
I have to protect you
from yourself.

146
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:18,167
And you made a choice.

147
00:09:19,433 --> 00:09:21,233
And it wasn't me.

148
00:09:26,533 --> 00:09:29,100
I can't bear it
when I left you.

149
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:31,267
I almost went crazy.

150
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:06,167
I almost went crazy.

151
00:10:06,233 --> 00:10:08,200
I'm always thinking
if you ate already...

152
00:10:08,267 --> 00:10:09,833
who is feeding you?

153
00:10:09,900 --> 00:10:10,933
If you are sick...

154
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:13,767
when you're so fussy.

155
00:10:14,267 --> 00:10:15,700
Who will take care of you?

156
00:10:15,767 --> 00:10:17,400
You're so fussy.

157
00:10:22,767 --> 00:10:26,133
I couldn't take that
I went back to you.

158
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:28,400
I ate all my pride.

159
00:10:31,833 --> 00:10:35,167
I ate all my pride
to go back to you.

160
00:10:35,900 --> 00:10:37,367
So, the mission of the company

161
00:10:37,433 --> 00:10:39,300
that I'm actually presenting
to you

162
00:10:39,367 --> 00:10:42,967
would be to address basic
necessities of people

163
00:10:43,033 --> 00:10:44,933
for their daily lives.

164
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:48,800
To produce products that
would help them,

165
00:10:48,867 --> 00:10:50,667
just you know, with simple
decision making.

166
00:10:50,733 --> 00:10:53,200
Like for example as simple
as a sock...

167
00:10:53,267 --> 00:10:56,867
produce socks that are
good quality material.

168
00:10:56,933 --> 00:11:00,600
Produce t-shirts, round necks,
good fit...

169
00:11:00,667 --> 00:11:02,200
that can fit any body type

170
00:11:02,267 --> 00:11:08,233
with just so you know, neutral
colors, black, red, beige,

171
00:11:08,333 --> 00:11:13,167
gray, and also eventually
kind of produce also dresses

172
00:11:13,233 --> 00:11:15,900
that are more for live it up,
like you know,

173
00:11:15,967 --> 00:11:20,600
a coffee date with a friend
that has florals...

174
00:11:23,500 --> 00:11:25,067
I was too late.

175
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:31,633
I think I don't know you
that well.

176
00:11:34,067 --> 00:11:37,200
I thought I am included
in your dreams.

177
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:43,900
I thought I am included in the
life that you want to fulfill.

178
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:45,667
But I was wrong.

179
00:11:47,400 --> 00:11:49,933
You are willing to give up
everything.

180
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:51,567
You are willing to forget
everything...

181
00:11:51,633 --> 00:11:52,600
No.

182
00:11:52,667 --> 00:11:55,300
Just to fulfill everything
that you want.

183
00:11:56,033 --> 00:11:58,900
- That's not true.
- It is.

184
00:12:20,900 --> 00:12:23,300
Oh my gosh.

185
00:12:23,367 --> 00:12:27,600
I still can't believe that
they liked my presentation.

186
00:12:28,867 --> 00:12:30,500
Why not?

187
00:12:30,567 --> 00:12:32,233
You were so good earlier.

188
00:12:32,300 --> 00:12:34,467
You caught their attention.

189
00:12:35,600 --> 00:12:37,367
All thanks to you.

190
00:12:38,367 --> 00:12:40,233
But you know what, Tiffany?

191
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:43,167
I can't take all the credit.

192
00:12:43,233 --> 00:12:44,933
Because the truth is,

193
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:49,433
I guided you to the direction
that you should reach.

194
00:12:49,533 --> 00:12:56,233
Exactly, that's why I can't
do all this if not for you.

195
00:12:57,600 --> 00:12:59,700
You know, you should watch
where you're going.

196
00:12:59,767 --> 00:13:01,200
Do you own this road?

197
00:13:01,267 --> 00:13:03,067
Why? Do you own this road?

198
00:13:03,133 --> 00:13:04,900
You're crazy, right?

199
00:13:08,300 --> 00:13:13,267
Don't worry, I'll bring you pili
next time we meet.

200
00:13:13,333 --> 00:13:15,400
You made a smile a bit.

201
00:13:15,467 --> 00:13:17,633
Thanks for making me smile.

202
00:13:19,500 --> 00:13:21,433
For you, it's free.

203
00:13:21,533 --> 00:13:24,067
Sweets for good vibes.

204
00:13:24,833 --> 00:13:26,167
Bye.

205
00:13:26,233 --> 00:13:27,567
Bye, Miss Pili.

206
00:13:27,633 --> 00:13:31,033
By the way, that's more
delicious if it's not expired.

207
00:13:31,100 --> 00:13:32,300
What?

208
00:13:34,333 --> 00:13:35,667
Basti is my boyfriend.

209
00:13:35,733 --> 00:13:37,133
Right, Babe?

210
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:38,833
Yes, Sir.

211
00:13:54,300 --> 00:13:56,600
A grouchy person becomes ugly.

212
00:13:56,700 --> 00:13:58,200
Like this.

213
00:13:59,100 --> 00:14:01,633
- Oh my gosh.
- That suits you.

214
00:14:01,700 --> 00:14:03,100
Just be happy.

215
00:14:04,400 --> 00:14:06,033
Sweetie pie, come on.

216
00:14:06,100 --> 00:14:07,600
Let's go to sleep.

217
00:14:20,733 --> 00:14:24,400
Basti, who would not be jealous?

218
00:14:24,467 --> 00:14:27,200
Your dimples attract girls.

219
00:14:27,267 --> 00:14:31,067
I fell in love
with your dimples.

220
00:14:32,867 --> 00:14:36,467
I just want you to taste
my mother's cooking

221
00:14:36,533 --> 00:14:39,400
but if you're not in the mood,
that's okay.

222
00:14:39,467 --> 00:14:41,067
I'll leave.

223
00:14:44,867 --> 00:14:46,900
Oh my gosh, it's delicious.

224
00:14:46,967 --> 00:14:48,833
What is this?

225
00:14:48,900 --> 00:14:51,000
Stewed frog legs.

226
00:14:52,567 --> 00:14:53,700
Is that your parents?

227
00:14:53,767 --> 00:14:54,800
Oh my gosh.

228
00:14:54,867 --> 00:14:56,133
You know, you have to
introduce me to them

229
00:14:56,200 --> 00:14:57,600
as your girlfriend.

230
00:14:57,667 --> 00:14:59,933
Why are you afraid?

231
00:15:00,767 --> 00:15:02,633
So what, right?

232
00:15:19,967 --> 00:15:21,633
Thank you, Tiffany.

233
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:28,200
Well, I'll go ahead.

234
00:15:28,267 --> 00:15:29,900
It's already late.

235
00:15:32,533 --> 00:15:34,867
Do you want to have lunch
tomorrow?

236
00:15:35,833 --> 00:15:39,000
That's the least that I can do

237
00:15:39,067 --> 00:15:41,433
for everything that you did
for me.

238
00:15:42,400 --> 00:15:43,800
I'll invite Clau...

239
00:15:45,233 --> 00:15:46,933
if you're not busy.

240
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:50,400
Maybe I'm already taking
so much of your time.

241
00:15:50,467 --> 00:15:51,433
What?

242
00:15:52,400 --> 00:15:53,633
Game?

243
00:16:03,600 --> 00:16:05,633
Do you remember this movie?

244
00:16:05,700 --> 00:16:06,667
Yes.

245
00:16:06,733 --> 00:16:09,200
Until now, I still can't
understand the choices

246
00:16:09,300 --> 00:16:11,433
these characters make.

247
00:16:11,500 --> 00:16:14,467
It's because you are a very
logical person.

248
00:16:14,533 --> 00:16:19,133
In life, some people make
illogical choices.

249
00:16:19,200 --> 00:16:22,233
Plus, it's not good to
make into a movie

250
00:16:22,300 --> 00:16:24,567
the life of a logical person.

251
00:16:24,633 --> 00:16:26,333
There's no thrill.

252
00:16:27,233 --> 00:16:31,200
That's why I envy Celeste.

253
00:16:31,267 --> 00:16:36,700
She must be someone really
special to make you illogical

254
00:16:36,767 --> 00:16:38,700
and a little impulsive.

255
00:16:42,700 --> 00:16:46,167
You might think that I'm
illogical and impulsive.

256
00:16:46,233 --> 00:16:50,500
But if there's one decision
that I'm pretty sure of,

257
00:16:50,567 --> 00:16:53,967
it's getting married to Celeste.

258
00:16:54,033 --> 00:16:57,500
I'm really sure about
what I feel for her.

259
00:16:57,567 --> 00:17:00,633
Thank you so much for
bringing out the best in me.

260
00:17:00,700 --> 00:17:04,367
The best thing about me is you,
Love.

261
00:17:04,433 --> 00:17:06,667
You are amazing.

262
00:17:06,733 --> 00:17:10,433
You are worthy
and you are loved.

263
00:17:10,500 --> 00:17:12,200
And you are my home.

264
00:17:16,233 --> 00:17:19,800
I'm just really trying to find
my place with my career

265
00:17:19,867 --> 00:17:21,467
and with your family.

266
00:17:21,533 --> 00:17:22,967
Well, at the end of the day,

267
00:17:23,033 --> 00:17:26,200
what's important is that you
love me and I love you, right?

268
00:17:26,267 --> 00:17:27,600
Yes.

269
00:17:27,667 --> 00:17:30,233
Celeste, once in a while,

270
00:17:30,300 --> 00:17:32,233
right in the middle
of ordinary life,

271
00:17:32,300 --> 00:17:34,533
love gives you a fairy tale.

272
00:17:34,600 --> 00:17:38,100
Love, you have been my princess
for five long years.

273
00:17:38,167 --> 00:17:40,933
And it's now time to make you
my queen.

274
00:17:42,133 --> 00:17:46,900
Celeste, will you be
my happily ever after?

275
00:17:46,967 --> 00:17:48,433
Will you marry me?

276
00:17:50,600 --> 00:17:52,767
Of course.

277
00:17:52,833 --> 00:17:54,333
Yes.

278
00:17:59,167 --> 00:18:03,467
What do you think I should do
so it will be all right

279
00:18:03,533 --> 00:18:07,233
for your sister Vivian and
Tiffany can accept me?

280
00:18:07,300 --> 00:18:12,300
I'll give up my position,
my inheritance, the perks...

281
00:18:12,367 --> 00:18:15,533
just to prove how much
I love you.

282
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:18,933
If my family can't accept you
as my future wife,

283
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:21,800
life will still go on for us.

284
00:18:21,900 --> 00:18:27,033
Come hell or high water,
our wedding will push through.

285
00:18:36,533 --> 00:18:40,333
I'm happy that you are happy.

286
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:44,433
And I'm happy with your
found happiness.

287
00:18:45,100 --> 00:18:47,833
Because if there's one thing
that I'm sure of

288
00:18:47,900 --> 00:18:50,033
with the whole world,

289
00:18:50,100 --> 00:18:55,633
is that you deserve all the
happiness in the world.

290
00:18:55,733 --> 00:18:57,200
Cheers.

291
00:19:02,633 --> 00:19:03,867
One more.

292
00:19:05,800 --> 00:19:07,233
I think I had enough.

293
00:19:07,300 --> 00:19:09,567
Come on.
We're toasting you and Celeste.

294
00:19:09,633 --> 00:19:11,400
It's for good luck.

295
00:19:19,100 --> 00:19:21,400
But I'm not joking.

296
00:19:21,467 --> 00:19:23,467
I mean it.

297
00:19:23,533 --> 00:19:29,900
I'm very happy that you found
someone who makes you happy.

298
00:19:32,367 --> 00:19:34,567
Thank you, Aurelia.

299
00:19:34,633 --> 00:19:36,967
This really means a lot to me...

300
00:19:37,533 --> 00:19:40,000
that we're having this closure.

301
00:19:41,733 --> 00:19:45,433
And I promise you that
whatever choices

302
00:19:45,500 --> 00:19:47,700
or decisions you make,

303
00:19:47,767 --> 00:19:50,267
I will be supportive
and happy for you.

304
00:19:51,733 --> 00:19:59,600
And I promise you no matter
what happens, I'm just here.

305
00:19:59,667 --> 00:20:01,300
Cheers.

306
00:20:05,667 --> 00:20:07,133
Bottoms up.

307
00:20:12,233 --> 00:20:13,467
One more.

308
00:20:34,267 --> 00:20:35,333
More?

309
00:20:36,067 --> 00:20:37,467
Come on.

310
00:20:39,833 --> 00:20:41,233
Tonito?

311
00:20:55,700 --> 00:20:57,900
Oh, Tonito...

312
00:20:58,800 --> 00:21:04,400
until now you're still weak
when it comes to alcohol.

313
00:21:26,733 --> 00:21:29,900
I'm sure you will come back
to me.

314
00:21:33,133 --> 00:21:36,433
You're not a good fit
for Celeste.

315
00:21:38,767 --> 00:21:41,667
I'm the only one
who understands you.

316
00:21:43,167 --> 00:21:45,767
I had high hopes as well.

317
00:21:45,833 --> 00:21:51,567
I won't get married just
because you want

318
00:21:51,633 --> 00:21:56,533
or because it's good
for my parents' business.

319
00:21:57,900 --> 00:22:03,233
I'm not dumb to just follow
the orders of others.

320
00:22:03,300 --> 00:22:07,733
I genuinely love Tonito
and most of all,

321
00:22:07,800 --> 00:22:10,367
he's not hard to love.

322
00:22:10,433 --> 00:22:11,833
Tonito...

323
00:22:14,100 --> 00:22:18,567
can it be just
the two of us again?

324
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:25,200
Please, take me back.

325
00:22:26,400 --> 00:22:34,033
Please give us another chance.

326
00:22:34,100 --> 00:22:36,467
It's about Tonito.

327
00:22:36,533 --> 00:22:38,200
What about Tonito?

328
00:22:38,267 --> 00:22:45,067
I want him back and I will do
anything I can to take him back,

329
00:22:45,133 --> 00:22:48,967
and for him to go back
to my life and Tiffany's.

330
00:22:49,067 --> 00:22:53,767
If I were to set myself up
for another rejection,

331
00:22:53,833 --> 00:22:57,300
it must be for something
worth fighting for.

332
00:22:57,367 --> 00:23:02,500
I still love Tonito more than
I would ever admit.

333
00:23:04,433 --> 00:23:09,300
That's why I don't mind being
rejected over and over again

334
00:23:09,367 --> 00:23:11,433
as long as it's for him.

335
00:24:20,200 --> 00:24:22,433
So everything is my fault now?

336
00:24:23,833 --> 00:24:27,567
Why are you so hung up
who between us is at fault?

337
00:24:28,933 --> 00:24:31,100
Because that's what
you make me feel.

338
00:24:31,167 --> 00:24:33,600
You always tell me
it's my fault!

339
00:24:33,667 --> 00:24:34,733
I'm the one who has a problem!

340
00:24:34,800 --> 00:24:37,367
I'm the one who left!
I'm selfish!

341
00:24:38,300 --> 00:24:41,233
You're turning the tables on me!
You are like that!

342
00:24:42,533 --> 00:24:45,367
Always, always, always, it's me!

343
00:24:45,433 --> 00:24:47,733
Why are you doing this to me?

344
00:24:47,800 --> 00:24:50,600
I hate you! I hate you!

345
00:24:51,467 --> 00:24:54,900
Why do you have to always
be the nice one?

346
00:25:33,033 --> 00:25:34,600
Good thing you're here.

347
00:25:34,667 --> 00:25:35,867
What are you doing here?

348
00:25:35,967 --> 00:25:37,467
Where have you been?

349
00:25:37,533 --> 00:25:39,000
Who's with you?

350
00:25:39,067 --> 00:25:41,867
I'm the one who was left behind
and I'm wrong.

351
00:25:41,933 --> 00:25:42,967
I'm the bad one.

352
00:25:43,033 --> 00:25:44,833
I'm the one who forgot.

353
00:25:44,900 --> 00:25:46,133
It's always me.

354
00:25:46,200 --> 00:25:48,867
I think it has something to do
with Hazel coming back here.

355
00:25:48,933 --> 00:25:51,533
Maybe you will not fight
with me here, Celeste.

356
00:25:51,600 --> 00:25:53,467
You had a fight with me
and I'm pissed off.

357
00:25:53,533 --> 00:25:55,167
If you two will get married,

358
00:25:55,233 --> 00:25:57,667
your girlfriend Tiffany
will become a resident here.

359
00:25:57,733 --> 00:25:59,867
Tiffany and I will not break up.

360
00:25:59,933 --> 00:26:01,467
Right, Sugar pie?

361
00:26:03,333 --> 00:26:05,700
I'm not comfortable with Celeste
being here.

362
00:26:05,767 --> 00:26:08,000
If only she can leave Sorsogon.

363
00:26:08,067 --> 00:26:10,000
Tonito will be tied to Celeste
once he gets married

364
00:26:10,100 --> 00:26:12,900
and you know we don't want
to lose.

365
00:26:12,967 --> 00:26:15,933
It's my turn to expose
something.

366
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:18,300
She can feel what
Aurelia and I have?

367
00:26:18,367 --> 00:26:21,133
The mere fact that you
didn't tell that,

368
00:26:21,200 --> 00:26:23,367
that means you're hiding
something.

369
00:26:23,433 --> 00:26:25,767
We've met but we're not
destined.

370
00:26:25,833 --> 00:26:32,167
Maybe you and Mikoy are
destined in the end, right?

371
00:26:32,233 --> 00:26:33,533
I'm thrilled.
